OL,6,FHowever, he said that where Connor
OL,7,Fdied was three kilometres away and a
OL,8,Fsearch may not have resulted in him
OL,9,Fbeing found.
OL,11,FMr Spinney felt there was no need to
OL,12,Fplace any further orders to prevent
OL,13,Ffuture deaths as he said he was aware
OL,14,Fthat a number of policy changes had
OL,15,Fbeen made by the Ministry of Defence
OL,16,Fand that he knew that, Connor's death
OL,17,Fwas still very much on their minds.
