OL,3,CMental health failings contributed to
OL,4,Cmarine's death, inquest told
OL,6,F"As the MoD's actions, inactions and
OL,7,Ffailings have once again been brought
OL,8,Fto light, it is beyond clear that a
OL,9,Fchange within the MoD is long overdue.
OL,11,F"Lessons need to be learnt and
OL,12,Fimmediate changes made to prevent
OL,13,Ffuture loss of life. This is a tragic
OL,14,Fcase which included a Doctor who, in
OL,15,Fhis mind was trying to help Connor,
OL,16,Fbut who failed to follow policy in
OL,17,Freferring Connor on at the moment he
OL,18,Fneeded it most.
